{{Coord|28.187816|N|83.991492|E|type:edu|display=title}} {{Infobox academic division | name = Institute of Forestry | native_name = वन विज्ञान अध्ययन संस्थान | image = <!-- Tribhuwan University logo.jpg --> | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = Logo of [[Tribhuvan University]] | motto = | motto_lang = | motto_eng = | former_names = | established = 1947 | closed = | type = Public | parent = [[Tribhuvan University]] | affiliation = | city = [[Pokhara]] | canton = | prefecture = | province = | region = | state = | country = Nepal | coor = | dean = Dr. Krishna Raj Tiwari | rector = | principal = | director = | head_label = | head = | academic_staff = <!-- or |faculty= --> | students = <!-- or |enrollment= --> | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | alumni = | symbol = | website = http://www.iof.edu.np/ | logo = | footnotes = | embedded = }}
The '''Institute of Forestry''' ('''IoF''', {{lang-ne|वन विज्ञान अध्ययन संस्थान}}) is one of the five technical institutes under [[Tribhuvan University]], Nepal's largest academic institution. Under the Department of Forests, the IoF was founded as Nepal Forestry Institute in 1947 in [[Singha Durbar]]. However, it was relocated to [[Bhimphedi]] in 1957, then to [[Hetauda]] in 1965, before being incorporated into TU from 1972. The current head office of the institute, usually referred to as the ''dean's office'', is housed at Pokhara Campus.<ref name="iofpc">{{cite web|title=About us|url=http://www.iofpc.edu.np/about-us|website=iofpc.edu.np|publisher=Institute of Forestry, Pokhara Campus|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref><ref name="tu">{{cite web|title=Institute of Forestry|url=http://tribhuvan-university.edu.np/institutes/institute-of-forestry/|website=tribhuvan-university.edu.np|publisher=[[Tribhuvan University]]|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref>
The IoF implements forestry-related academic programs through its two constituent campuses, located in [[Pokhara]] and [[Hetauda]].<ref name="edu">{{cite web|title=Institute of Forestry, Pokhara Campus|url=http://edusanjal.com/college/institute-forestry-pokhara-campus|website=edusanjal.com|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref> The current dean of the institute is Krishna Raj Tiwari, and he is backed by two assistant deans, presently Yajna P. Timilsina and Jeev Nath Pandey.<ref name="iof">{{cite web|title=Administration at the Institute of Forestry|url=http://www.iof.edu.np/administration/|website=iof.edu.np|publisher=Institute of Foresty|accessdate=29 September 2016}}</ref>
==See also== The other technical institutes at TU are: * [[Institute of Agriculture and Animal Science]] * [[Institute of Engineering]] * [[Institute of Medicine, Nepal|Institute of Medicine]] * [[Institute of Science and Technology, Nepal|Institute of Science and Technology]]
